That‚Äôs why there is a ‚Äútime value of carbon‚Äù, and today‚Äôs solutions are always better for addressing climate change that tomorrow‚Äôs hypothetical ones.
A climate solution deployed today does 26 times more work on the atmosphere  by 2050 than a same sized solution developed in 2049.

The other thing to know ‚Äî early climate solutions always work better than later ones.That‚Äôs because climate solutions are *cumulative* over time. They avoid or remove X gigatons per year, over a period of Y years.
So let‚Äôs focus on deploying the solutions we have, and investing R&D dollars on possible, future ones.

Think of it this way: Let‚Äôs say you have a deadly illness, and you need to address it now.‚ÄúSolutions‚Äù are things that make a difference, now.Stuff that‚Äôs still in the lab, and not really available, and ‚Äúpossible future solutions‚Äù. And most won‚Äôt ever arrive.

Other things, which might *someday* scale to this size ‚Äî like DAC, CCS, fusion, whatever ‚Äî aren‚Äôt solutions. They are ‚Äúpossible, future solutions‚Äù.They might someday work. Or not. But they‚Äôre not really here yet.
